  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with a comprehensive legal framework designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute such activities. Here's an overview of the key legal aspects:\n\n1. International Frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Counter-Terrorism Financing regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n\n3. Legal Components\n- Criminalization of money laundering activities\n- Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n- Enhanced due diligence procedures\n- Asset seizure and forfeiture provisions\n\n4. Regulatory Oversight\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- International cooperation mechanisms\n\n5. Compliance Requirements\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Customer identification\n- Risk assessment\n- Reporting suspicious activities\n- Maintaining detailed transaction records\n\n6. Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset forfeiture\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\nThe framework aims to prevent criminal financial activities and protect the global financial system's integrity.",
